Fintech Focus for : The Revival of Local Distilleries



Fintech Focus












August 2013


































 




Craft Beer Hits Hotel Taps
The most commonly asked question at bars today is “what  kind of local beer do you have?” �To  expand their answer, hotels nationwide are embracing the rapid growth of the  craft beer industry, which has more than doubled in sales over the last six  years. 
In addition to smaller boutique hotels, several  large hotel chains like the Four Seasons Hotel, Fairmont Hotels, and Sheraton are now offering an extensive craft beer selection to guests and  providing a taste of the local community.
With the success of the product,  hotels are also expanding partnerships with local breweries to produce their  own in house brews and tailor promotions around featured beers for not only  hotel guests, but area locals.






New York Distilleries Make a Comeback
A little more than a century ago, New York consisted of  thousands of distilleries that produced whiskey, gin, and a variety of other spirits to  customers throughout the country. However, once Prohibition hit in 1920, all  taps went dry and production either went extinct or underground.
With the repeal of Prohibition in 1933, liquor production  was only feasible for a few large distilleries. It wasn’t until the 21st  century, that small boutique distilleries in New York began their revival, motivating  distillers to utilize the state’s locally grown organic farm products to start  up once again.
Today, New York is home to 30 craft distilleries and alcohol  production is one of the state’s fastest growing industries. The rebirth of New  York’s distilling industry has led to diversified product placement in  restaurants, liquor stores, and farmers markets - making a great economic impact  on the area.









Kelly Fuels Inc.Kelly  Fuels, Inc. is a nine store chain located in the heart of Central Michigan.  Their mission is to provide the highest quality products, with friendly  service, in a clean and safe environment.
Recently,  Kelly Fuels rolled out a new train depot logo in a majority of its stores. The new  design includes oversized train wheels located over the ‘Express Checkout’ and  features bold, bright and contrasting colors.
Kelly  Fuels was featured in Convenience Store Decisions magazine and was awarded  ‘Best Original Store Design, Honorable Mention’ by Convenience Store  News.
“We have been partners with Fintech for  over 10 years.  The ability to centralize our payments for beer and wine  purchases allows us to eliminate a task from our store managers, freeing them  up for the many other responsibilities that they have, and gives us confidence that  these transactions are handled effectively and efficiently.” – John L. Olds,  CFO of Kelly Fuels Inc.
3 Stacks Smoke & Tap House    3 Stacks Smoke & Tap House opened in February 2013  and is located in Frisco, Texas. The restaurant is named for the three large smokers that welcome diners upon entrance, each dedicated to  a different selection of meat.
3 Stacks aims to have customers taste the difference, by  serving a menu filled with quality slow smoked meats, homemade rubs &  sauces, seasonal side vegetables and daily baked breads.
Partners Trace Arnold and Jason Hall are committed to  serving quality, seasonal and fresh ingredients daily. Balancing the  extensive food menu is an all-American Tap House offering an extensive list  of local craft and regional beers.
"Fintech makes it simple to pay for our  liquor, beer and wine. We have an account with them and they pay the vendors  for us. Great deal, makes our life easier," - Jason Hall, Owner of 3  Stacks Smoke & Tap House
















