binarsEventsPhotosArticlesNewsBlogsPress ReleasesMedia Kit / Editorial CalendarProject HelpBloggersStoreSearch!   Get the latest news & insightsSubscribe     Two emerging brands pick starrdesign for prototype designsDec. 15, 2016Original Chopshop and Ruggles Green, two emerging restaurants based in Phoenix and Houston, respectively, have selected starrdesign to create prototype designs for both concept's units, according to a press release. The process includes architecture, operational analysis, design and brand development."We really love working with emerging brands, and while both concepts are established within their markets, we are excited to help further position them for long term growth,"Steve Starr, principal, starrdesign said in a news release. "We love both the food and the values that helped create Original ChopShop and Ruggles Green, and we look forward to bringing these core values to life in the space."Original ChopShop serves protein bowls, salads, acai bowls, fresh squeezed juices, sandwiches and protein shakes, while Ruggles Green serves burgers, pizza, pasta and salad. The former CEO of Zoe's Kitchen, Jason Morgan, was tapped to be both concept's CEO."I have worked with the team at starrdesign for many years and have been impressed with the quality of their work and the creative concepts they have produced," Morgan said."We look forward to collaborating on the evolution of the Original ChopShop and Ruggles Green brands and prototypes."Topics: Customer Service / Experience, Franchising & Growth, Marketing / Branding / Promotion, Operations Management, Restaurant Design / Layout, SustainabilitySponsored Links:Related Content10 things to avoid when launching a mobile appWhat's the state of the fast casual industry?The Halal Guys loyalty story to headline July 13 webinarRestaurant industry's Q1 end in 'some wins, some losses'Latest ContentOnslaught of Chipotle suits: 2 diners file, 7 other law firms form investor class actionsChipotle and the 'elepha